00019         
00020         // skip some internals
00021         if(c->namespaces->at(namespaceID).name == "maven")
00022                 if(c->namespaces->at(namespaceID).objects->at(objectID)->name == "Object" ||
00023                    c->namespaces->at(namespaceID).objects->at(objectID)->name == "String" ||
00024                    c->namespaces->at(namespaceID).objects->at(objectID)->name == "System" ||

00030         // C++ has a completely different way of dealing with static data members,
00031         // so it's easier to just stick the variables into a predictable namespace.

00033                 c->mapFileHandle << "  namespace " << c->namespaces->at(namespaceID).objects->at(objectID)->name

00036                         if(!c->namespaces->at(namespaceID).objects->at(objectID)->variables->at(k).isExternal &&
00037                            c->namespaces->at(namespaceID).objects->at(objectID)->variables->at(k).isStatic) {
00038                                 c->mapFileHandle << "    static ";
00039                                 string type = cType(findObjectPath(c, c->namespaces->at(namespaceID).objects->at(objectID)->variables->at(k).type));
00040                                 if(type == MAVEN_INVALID)
00041                                         c->mapFileHandle << "int"; // this for an enum
00042                                 else c->mapFileHandle << type;
00043                                 c->mapFileHandle << " " << c->namespaces->at(namespaceID).objects->at(objectID)->variables->at(k).name;
00044                                 if(c->namespaces->at(namespaceID).objects->at(objectID)->variables->at(k).defaultValue != "")
00045                                         c->mapFileHandle << " = " <<
00046                                           c->namespaces->at(namespaceID).objects->at(objectID)->variables->at(k).defaultValue;
00047                                 c->mapFileHandle << ";" << endl;
00048                         }
00049                 }
00050                 c->mapFileHandle << "  }\n";
00051         }
00052         
00053         if((c->namespaces->at(namespaceID).objects->at(objectID)->variables->length() -
00054                 countStaticVariables(c, namespaceID, objectID)) + countClassMethods(c, namespaceID, objectID) > 0) {
00055                 c->mapFileHandle << "  class " << c->namespaces->at(namespaceID).objects->at(objectID)->name;
00056                 if(c->namespaces->at(namespaceID).objects->at(objectID)->extends != "") {
00057                         // classes can be extended by multiple classes, so lets split them up
00058                         c->mapFileHandle << " : public ";
00059                         StringList extendList = split(',', c->namespaces->at(namespaceID).objects->at(objectID)->extends);
00060                         c->mapFileHandle << cType(findObjectPath(c, extendList[0], false));
00061                         for(int ei = 1; ei < extendList.length(); ++ei)
00062                                 c->mapFileHandle << "," << cType(findObjectPath(c, extendList[namespaceID], false));
00063                 }
00064                 c->mapFileHandle << " {" << endl;
00065                 
00066                 // non-static variable members
00067                 for(int k = 0; k < c->namespaces->at(namespaceID).objects->at(objectID)->variables->length(); ++k) {
00068                         if(!c->namespaces->at(namespaceID).objects->at(objectID)->variables->at(k).isStatic &&
00069                            !c->namespaces->at(namespaceID).objects->at(objectID)->variables->at(k).isInherited) {
00070                                 c->mapFileHandle << "    ";
00071                                 if(c->namespaces->at(namespaceID).objects->at(objectID)->variables->at(k).isPublic)
00072                                         c->mapFileHandle << "public: ";
00073                                 else c->mapFileHandle << "protected: ";

00075                                 if(type == MAVEN_INVALID)
00076                                         c->mapFileHandle << "int"; // this for an enum

00079                                 if(c->namespaces->at(namespaceID).objects->at(objectID)->variables->at(k).defaultValue != "")
00080                                         c->mapFileHandle << " = " << c->namespaces->at(namespaceID).objects->at(objectID)->variables->at(k).defaultValue;
00081                                 c->mapFileHandle << ";" << endl;
00082                         }
00083                 }
00084                 
00085                 // constructors, super() is injected into all constructors.
00086                 MavenVariables args;
00087                 if(findFunctionID(c, namespaceID, objectID, c->namespaces->at(namespaceID).objects->at(objectID)->name, args, true) < 0) {
00088                         c->mapFileHandle << "    public: " << c->namespaces->at(namespaceID).objects->at(objectID)->name << "() { super(\"";
00089                         c->mapFileHandle << c->namespaces->at(namespaceID).name << "." << c->namespaces->at(namespaceID).objects->at(objectID)->name << "\"); } " << endl;
00090                 }
00091

00093                 for(int k = 0; k < c->namespaces->at(namespaceID).objects->at(objectID)->functions->length(); ++k) {
00094                         if(!c->namespaces->at(namespaceID).objects->at(objectID)->functions->at(k).isExported &&
00095                            !c->namespaces->at(namespaceID).objects->at(objectID)->functions->at(k).isInherited) {
00096                                 c->mapFileHandle << "    ";
00097                                 if(c->namespaces->at(namespaceID).objects->at(objectID)->functions->at(k).isPublic)
00098                                         c->mapFileHandle << "public: ";

00100                                 if(c->namespaces->at(namespaceID).objects->at(objectID)->functions->at(k).isStatic)
00101                                         c->mapFileHandle << "static ";
00102                                 else if(c->namespaces->at(namespaceID).objects->at(objectID)->functions->at(k).name !=
00103                                                 c->namespaces->at(namespaceID).objects->at(objectID)->name)
00104                                         c->mapFileHandle << "virtual ";
00105                                 
00106                                 if(c->namespaces->at(namespaceID).objects->at(objectID)->functions->at(k).returnType != "<constructor>")
00107                                         c->mapFileHandle << cType(findObjectPath(c, c->namespaces->at(namespaceID).objects->at(objectID)->functions->at(k).returnType));
00108                                 
00109                                 // function arguments can't be static
00110                                 for(int i = 0; i < c->namespaces->at(namespaceID).objects->at(objectID)->functions->at(k).args.length(); ++i)
00111                                         c->namespaces->at(namespaceID).objects->at(objectID)->functions->at(k).args[i].isStatic = false;
00112                                 
00113                                 c->mapFileHandle << " " << c->namespaces->at(namespaceID).objects->at(objectID)->functions->at(k).name << "("
00114                                                                 << c->namespaces->at(namespaceID).objects->at(objectID)->functions->at(k).args.getCPP(c) << ");" << endl;
